It also seems to encourage database maintenance problems
for one administrative authority to handle 100 separate domains,
as CSNET has had to do.  The general ratio should be one domain
per administrative authority, it seems to me.  When you are juggling
100 separate entities, it is easier to make mistakes than
if all your data were integrated at your level.
